EventApi__Calendar_Reminder_Text__c:
There is no better place for professional development than the Annual Conference & Exposition. By attending, you'll gain the tools and resources you need to implement successful practices which help your company succeed. 

An organization may conduct its business at the annual general meeting. The business may include electing a board of directors, making important decisions regarding the organization, and informing the members of previous and future activities. At this meeting, the shareholders and partners may receive copies of the company's accounts, review fiscal information for the past year, and ask any questions regarding the directions the business will take in the future.

At the annual general meeting, the president or chairman of the organization presides over the meeting and may give an overall status of the organization. The secretary prepares the minutes and may be asked to read important papers. The treasurer may present a financial report. Other officers, the board of directors, and committees may give their reports. Attending this meeting are the members or the shareholders of the organization, depending on the type of organization.

EventApi__Overview_HTML__c:
World Renowned Event


There is no better place for professional development than theÂ Annual Conference & Exposition. By attending, you'll gain the tools and resources you need to implement successful practices which help your company succeed.Â 


Â 


Fresh PerspectivesÂ 


Internationally-renowned speakers that offer fresh points of view and inspiring stories that can help shift your perspectives and deepen your understanding of leadership, motivation, and success.Â 


Â 


Comprehensive LearningÂ 


Over 200 concurrent sessionsÂ provide a complete education for professionals at every stage of their career. You?ll be able to choose from a broad range of topics so you can customize the learning you need.Â Concentrate on solutions designed to help your organization become more compliant; delve into the cutting-edge trends that will impact your workplace in the next few years; build a strategic talent management plan to increase engagement and retention.Â Innovative learning opportunities, such as: -Â Our Masters Series featuring high-level academicians -Â Presentations covering exciting new practices -Â Practitioner Exchange sessions featuring professionalsÂ -Â PreconferenceÂ WorkshopsÂ andÂ SeminarsÂ that dive deeperÂ into essentials. - Recertification creditsÂ for your general designation.


Â 


Extraordinary NetworkingÂ 


From our vast Exposition HallÂ to our session-based networking, to the hallways of the convention center, there is ample opportunity for you to meet HR professionals who share your goals and your challenges. Plus online networking! Attendees getÂ access to our Conference Community siteÂ where you can meet and chat with other attendees and build connections with them before you even get here. And there?s alwaysÂ Twitter,Â FacebookÂ andÂ LinkedIn.Â 


Â 


Endless Solutions


The world?s largest marketplace, theÂ Exposition,Â gives you access to thousands of solutions-providers in every industry.Â Interested in becoming a sponsor or exhibitor? VisitÂ fun.fonteva.comÂ for more information.




Still not convinced that you need to be here? See more in outÂ Why AttendÂ page.

EventApi__Description__c: Awards ceremonies are a celebration of talent, success and achievement for your loyal members. Awards ceremonies are employed by all sorts of sectors as a way to celebrate the success of an individual, a team, or an entire firm or company.
EventApi__Overview_HTML__c:
Â 


Â 


Â 


Co-chairs, Brian Ortega and Miriam Nelson, invite you to kick off the 37th annualÂ gala with cocktails, hors d'oeuvres and pre-dinner festivities commencing at 5:30 PM.


Â 


Pre-dinner festivities include a silent auction and entertaining gala experiences for all including a wine wall presented by Top Ten Liquors where guests can purchase wine to drink during the evening or to take home. Enjoy viewing select silent auction items, take a chance at our every-body wins punch walls and other exciting experiences while connecting with friends.

Name: FON-Press Conference - Invite Only (Lightning Event)
EventApi__Description__c: An invite only press conference is a meeting, organized for the purposes of officially distributing information to the media and answering questions from reporters. In general a corporate press conference is led by the company's executive management or his or her appointed press liaison. Occasionally, given limited resources, particularly during a time of quarterly or annual earnings, can also be issued in response to addressing public relations issues.

EventApi__Business_Group__r.Name: FON-International Association

Name: FON-Meet the Organization 1-1 Meetings (Lightning Event)
EventApi__Description__c: A 1-1 is a dedicated space for employees to convene in open-ended and anticipated conversation. Unlike status reports or tactical meetings, the 1-1 meeting is a place for coaching, mentorship, giving context, or even venting.
EventApi__Overview_HTML__c:
Â 


Our meetup will be hosted by Fonteva co-founder and CEO, Jerry Huskins. He will discuss Fonteva Salesforce solutions and host guests for drinks and networking in our Arlington, VA office. Fonteva is the #1 Salesforce AMS provider and #1 ISV in North America. Under his leadership, Fonteva has grown into a leader in the Salesforce space, currently ranked 286 on Inc Magazine's "500 list" of fastest growing companies in the US. His 33-year career in technology services, product development, business process modeling and strategic finance spans both Fortune 500 and early stage company.Â 


Â 


During this event you will also have the chance to setup 1-1 meetings with different employees within the organization.


Â 


Â

EventApi__Business_Group__r.Name: FON-International Association

Name: FON-Webinar - Our Mission - Free Event (Lightning Event)
EventApi__Description__c: A webinar is a presentation, lecture, workshop or seminar that is transmitted over the Web using video conferencing software. A key feature of a Webinar is its interactive elements is the ability to give, receive and discuss information in real-time from virtually anywhere with an internet connection. Participants can share audio, documents and applications with webinar attendees.
EventApi__Overview_HTML__c:
Please join us to learn more about our mission and how you can help us advance it. You will learn about theÂ organization, its history and pioneers, and how we help organizations implement effective change using a behavioral science approach to solve critical business challenges.


Â 


You will gain insight into the role of the professional and how you can help senior leaders resolve critical business challenges through problem solving, decision making, collecting feedback, implementing effective solutions, and measuring results.Â 


Â 


Â

EventApi__Calendar_Reminder_Text__c:
There is no better place for professional development than the Annual Conference & Exposition. By attending, you'll gain the tools and resources you need to implement successful practices which help your company succeed. 

An organization may conduct its business at the annual general meeting. The business may include electing a board of directors, making important decisions regarding the organization, and informing the members of previous and future activities. At this meeting, the shareholders and partners may receive copies of the company's accounts, review fiscal information for the past year, and ask any questions regarding the directions the business will take in the future.

At the annual general meeting, the president or chairman of the organization presides over the meeting and may give an overall status of the organization. The secretary prepares the minutes and may be asked to read important papers. The treasurer may present a financial report. Other officers, the board of directors, and committees may give their reports. Attending this meeting are the members or the shareholders of the organization, depending on the type of organization.

EventApi__Overview_HTML__c:
World Renowned Event


There is no better place for professional development than theÂ Annual Conference & Exposition. By attending, you'll gain the tools and resources you need to implement successful practices which help your company succeed.Â 


Â 


Fresh PerspectivesÂ 


Internationally-renowned speakers that offer fresh points of view and inspiring stories that can help shift your perspectives and deepen your understanding of leadership, motivation, and success.Â 


Â 


Comprehensive LearningÂ 


Over 200 concurrent sessionsÂ provide a complete education for professionals at every stage of their career. You?ll be able to choose from a broad range of topics so you can customize the learning you need.Â Concentrate on solutions designed to help your organization become more compliant; delve into the cutting-edge trends that will impact your workplace in the next few years; build a strategic talent management plan to increase engagement and retention.Â Innovative learning opportunities, such as: -Â Our Masters Series featuring high-level academicians -Â Presentations covering exciting new practices -Â Practitioner Exchange sessions featuring professionalsÂ -Â PreconferenceÂ WorkshopsÂ andÂ SeminarsÂ that dive deeperÂ into essentials. - Recertification creditsÂ for your general designation.


Â 


Extraordinary NetworkingÂ 


From our vast Exposition HallÂ to our session-based networking, to the hallways of the convention center, there is ample opportunity for you to meet HR professionals who share your goals and your challenges. Plus online networking! Attendees getÂ access to our Conference Community siteÂ where you can meet and chat with other attendees and build connections with them before you even get here. And there?s alwaysÂ Twitter,Â FacebookÂ andÂ LinkedIn.Â 


Â 


Endless Solutions


The world?s largest marketplace, theÂ Exposition,Â gives you access to thousands of solutions-providers in every industry.Â Interested in becoming a sponsor or exhibitor? VisitÂ fun.fonteva.comÂ for more information.




Still not convinced that you need to be here? See more in outÂ Why AttendÂ page.

At the annual general meeting, the president or chairman of the organization presides over the meeting and may give an overall status of the organization. The secretary prepares the minutes and may be asked to read important papers. The treasurer may present a financial report. Other officers, the board of directors, and committees may give their reports. Attending this meeting are the members or the shareholders of the organization, depending on the type of organization.
EventApi__Overview_HTML__c:
World Renowned Event


There is no better place for professional development than theÂ Annual Conference & Exposition. By attending, you'll gain the tools and resources you need to implement successful practices which help your company succeed.Â 


Â 


Fresh PerspectivesÂ 


Internationally-renowned speakers that offer fresh points of view and inspiring stories that can help shift your perspectives and deepen your understanding of leadership, motivation, and success.Â 


Â 


Comprehensive LearningÂ 


Over 200 concurrent sessions provide a complete education for professionals at every stage of their career. You?ll be able to choose from a broad range of topics so you can customize the learning you need.Â Concentrate on solutions designed to help your organization become more compliant; delve into the cutting-edge trends that will impact your workplace in the next few years; build a strategic talent management plan to increase engagement and retention.Â Innovative learning opportunities, such as: -Â Our Masters Series featuring high-level academicians -Â Presentations covering exciting new practices -Â Practitioner Exchange sessions featuring professionalsÂ -Â PreconferenceÂ WorkshopsÂ andÂ SeminarsÂ that dive deeperÂ into essentials. - Recertification credits for your general designation.


Â 


Extraordinary NetworkingÂ 


From our vast Exposition HallÂ to our session-based networking, to the hallways of the convention center, there is ample opportunity for you to meet HR professionals who share your goals and your challenges. Plus online networking! Attendees getÂ access to our Conference Community site where you can meet and chat with other attendees and build connections with them before you even get here. And there?s alwaysÂ Twitter,Â FacebookÂ andÂ LinkedIn.Â 


Â 


Endless Solutions


The world?s largest marketplace, theÂ Exposition,Â gives you access to thousands of solutions-providers in every industry.Â Interested in becoming a sponsor or exhibitor? VisitÂ fun.fonteva.comÂ for more information.




Still not convinced that you need to be here? See more in outÂ Why Attend page.

EventApi__Business_Group__r.Name: FON-International Association

Name: FON-Meet the Organization 1-1 Meetings (Community Event)
EventApi__Description__c: A 1-1 is a dedicated space for employees to convene in open-ended and anticipated conversation. Unlike status reports or tactical meetings, the 1-1 meeting is a place for coaching, mentorship, giving context, or even venting.
EventApi__Overview_HTML__c:
Â 


Our meetup will be hosted by Fonteva co-founder and CEO, Jerry Huskins. He will discuss Fonteva Salesforce solutions and host guests for drinks and networking in our Arlington, VA office. Fonteva is the #1 Salesforce AMS provider and #1 ISV in North America. Under his leadership, Fonteva has grown into a leader in the Salesforce space, currently ranked 286 on Inc Magazine's "500 list" of fastest growing companies in the US. His 33-year career in technology services, product development, business process modeling and strategic finance spans both Fortune 500 and early stage company.Â 


Â 


During this event you will also have the chance to setup 1-1 meetings with different employees within the organization.


Â 


Â

EventApi__Business_Group__r.Name: FON-International Association

Name: FON-Press Conference-Invite Only (Community Event)
EventApi__Description__c: An invite only press conference is a meeting, organized for the purposes of officially distributing information to the media and answering questions from reporters. In general a corporate press conference is led by the company's executive management or his or her appointed press liaison. Occasionally, given limited resources, particularly during a time of quarterly or annual earnings, can also be issued in response to addressing public relations issues.

Name: FON-Webinar - Our Mission-Free Event (Community Event)
EventApi__Description__c: A webinar is a presentation, lecture, workshop or seminar that is transmitted over the Web using video conferencing software. A key feature of a Webinar is its interactive elements is the ability to give, receive and discuss information in real-time from virtually anywhere with an internet connection. Participants can share audio, documents and applications with webinar attendees.
EventApi__Display_Name__c: Webinar - Our Mission - Free Event (Community Event)
EventApi__Overview_HTML__c:
Please join us to learn more about our mission and how you can help us advance it. You will learn about theÂ organization, its history and pioneers, and how we help organizations implement effective change using a behavioral science approach to solve critical business challenges.


Â 


You will gain insight into the role of the professional and how you can help senior leaders resolve critical business challenges through problem solving, decision making, collecting feedback, implementing effective solutions, and measuring results.Â 


Â 


Â
